summary: Do you think Arya will marry Elmar Frey again?  He is the Frey she knows best, and they were betrothed away one point.  I wonder...
question: Do you think Arya will marry Elmar Frey again?  He is the Frey she knows best, and they were betrothed away one point.  I wonder if she'd confront him directly,  or if seeing him die might be part of what opens her eyes to the fact that Red Wedding 2.0 is atrocity, not justice.
answer:
Sorry, anon, did you mean she’ll meet Elmar Frey again? Yeah, maybe.

I think what really makes Arya think about the line between justice and revenge is meeting Lady Stoneheart, though.

summary: During the Joffrey-Nymeria incident while Arya was still missing Cersei convinced Jaime to find Arya and cut off her hand...
body:
During the Joffrey-Nymeria incident while Arya was still missing Cersei convinced Jaime to find Arya and cut off her hand (spoiler alert: he failed)

“My sister wanted the girl to lose a hand. The old penalty, for striking one of the blood royal. Robert told her she was cruel and mad. They fought for half the night … well, Cersei fought, and Robert drank. Past midnight, the queen summoned me inside. The king was passed out snoring on the Myrish carpet. I asked my sister if she wanted me to carry him to bed. She told me I should carry her to bed, and shrugged out of her robe. I took her on Raymun Darry’s bed after stepping over Robert. If His Grace had woken I would have killed him there and then. He would not have been the first king to die upon my sword … but you know that story, don’t you?“ He slashed at a tree branch, shearing it in half. "As I was fucking her, Cersei cried, ‘I want.’ I thought that she meant me, but it was the Stark girl that she wanted, maimed or dead.” The things I do for love. “It was only by chance that Stark’s own men found the girl before me. If I had come on her first …” - Jaime IV, AFfC

Considering the fact that he pushed Bran out of a tower there is a good chance that Jaime truly would have done it and he kind of admits that. Then fast forward to Jaime being held captive by the Brave Companions and loses his hand. 

“Sunlight ran silver along the edge of the arakh as it came shivering down, almost too fast to see. And Jaime screamed.” - Jaime III, ASoS

Honestly there is some vicious irony in that. Jaime once searched for Arya in order to exact a punishment ordered by Cersie and then he searches once again for Arya it is he who loses the hand.
